## ABAP Syntax Modernization Rules (with Java Anchors)
| Old ABAP | New ABAP | Java Anchor |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| MOVE source TO target. | target = source. | target = source; |
| ADD value TO target. | target = target + value. | target += value; |
| CONCATENATE a b INTO c. | c = \|{ a }{ b }\|. | c = a + b; |
| MOVE-CORRESPONDING src TO dst. | dst = CORRESPONDING #( src ). | BeanUtils.copyProperties() |
| CALL METHOD obj->m. | obj->m( ). | obj.method(); |
| CREATE OBJECT lo TYPE cl. | lo = NEW cl( ). | obj = new Cl(); |
| SUBTRACT val FROM target. | target = target - val. | target -= value; |
| TRANSLATE str TO UPPER CASE. | str = to_upper( str ). | str.toUpperCase() |
| DESCRIBE TABLE itab LINES n. | n = lines( itab ). | list.size() |

## RAP Quick Reference
- RAP = RESTful ABAP Programming Model (S/4HANA Clean Core)
- 3-layer: CDS View Entity -> Behavior Definition -> Service Binding
- Managed scenario: framework handles CRUD, numbering, draft
- Unmanaged scenario: custom ABAP logic for legacy integration
- EML: MODIFY ENTITIES, READ ENTITIES, COMMIT ENTITIES
- Behavior: validations, determinations, actions, side effects
- Draft: with draft; in behavior definition
- Authorization: global (static) + instance (row-level)
- Feature control: enable/disable fields and actions per instance
- Numbering: early (external), late (managed), unmanaged
- Testing: CDS Test Double Framework + behavior mocking
- CDS: define root view entity, composition, association
- Projection: define root view entity as projection on
- Abstract entity: for unstructured action parameters
- Service definition: expose <Entity> as <Alias>
- Service binding: OData V4 - UI or OData V4 - Web API
- Fiori Elements: auto-generated UI from CDS annotations
- Side effects: trigger field refresh after action/field change
- ETag: optimistic concurrency via @Semantics.systemDateTime.lastChangedAt
- Locking: exclusive lock via behavior definition
- Error handling: REPORTED, FAILED, MAPPED return structures

## Fiori Quick Reference
- Fiori Elements preferred over freestyle SAPUI5
- List Report + Object Page = most common floorplan
- CDS annotations drive UI: @UI.lineItem, @UI.facet, @UI.fieldGroup
- Value help: @Consumption.valueHelpDefinition
- Criticality: @UI.criticality mapped to status field
- Search: @Search.searchable, @Search.defaultSearchElement
- manifest.json: routing, targets, data sources
- Launchpad tiles: semantic object + action
- OData V4 model binding: {path: '/EntitySet'}
- Draft: automatic save/discard in Fiori Elements

